A look at the contents of the first cell

{% raw %} 
if files.valid:
    cells.iloc[0]
{% endraw %}

where the fields are:

  • t : MJD central time
  • tw : width
  • fexp : exposure for this interval compared to mean
  • n : Number of photons detected
  • w : List of int(weight*256) for the photons detected during the interval. stored as uint8
  • S, B : expected signal and background

An important check of the procedure is a comparison of the sum of weights in a cell with the exposure for that time interval.

{% raw %} 
if files.valid:
    wsum = cells.w.apply(np.sum)/256.;
    plt.semilogy(cells.fexp, (wsum/cells.fexp).clip(1e2,5e2), '.');
    plt.xlabel('exposure')
    plt.ylabel('sum of weights / exposure');
    plt.grid(alpha=0.5)
{% endraw %}
